## 4. Results & Evidence

Tested on four datasets across different task types:

| Dataset | Task Type | CRAG vs RAG | CRAG vs Self-RAG |
|---------|-----------|-------------|-----------------|
| PopQA | Short-form QA | +7.0% accuracy | — |
| Biography | Long-form generation | +14.9% FactScore | — |
| PubHealth | True/False (health) | +36.6% accuracy | — |
| Arc-Challenge | Multiple choice | +15.4% accuracy | — |

Self-CRAG (CRAG plugged into the Self-RAG framework) also outperformed Self-RAG alone on most benchmarks.

**Key findings from ablation studies:**

- Removing *any* single action (Correct, Incorrect, Ambiguous) hurts performance — all three matter
- Removing the Ambiguous action is especially damaging: without it, the system is brittle when the evaluator is uncertain
- Removing document refinement causes the largest single drop
- The T5 evaluator beats ChatGPT, ChatGPT-CoT, and ChatGPT-few-shot at retrieval assessment

**Computational overhead:**

| Method | TFLOPs/token | Time/instance |
|--------|-------------|---------------|
| RAG | 26.5 | 0.363s |
| CRAG | 27.2 | 0.512s |
| Self-RAG | 26.5–132.4 | 0.741s |
| Self-CRAG | 27.2–80.2 | 0.908s |

CRAG adds modest overhead while significantly improving correctness.

